rComments: I'm a fan! Bangu treated us like grown-ups and the assignments made a lot of sense. His examples are funny, and the explanations of concepts are very clear.
Loved this class! The topics were very interesting and clearly explained. And Bangu NEVER rambles.
Yeah, take your brains with you if you attend!! Excellent feedback on the written assignments.
I really enjoyed the class! Clear, interesting stuff. Find the comments here odd, you guys must have failed or what??!

I couldn't handle this class. Not interesting, hard to follow, just terrible in general.  I would have failed had it not been for the fact that we had English speaking TA's. Just like everyone else said, mandatory attendance = nap time. Stay away from this guy if you can.
terrible class. straight from powerpoints. not interesting at all. fell asleep every day. attendance mandatory

Professor Bangu teaches strictly from the book and PowerPoints. For you grammar freaks out there, he misspells/leaves out words which is kind of absurd to me, but that's just me. There's no philosophical debates and he doesn't explain well. I never, EVER want to go to class because I just fall asleep. The mandatory attendance is a definite killer.
Nevermind, I wrote that last post and decided that I was way too generous. Therefore, I am giving him all 1.0's to balance out the mistake :D -From a Chemical Engineering student

Pretty helpful through email but does a poor job of answering questions in full during lecture. Class is taught entirely through powerpoints and by the textbook, decreasing the philosophical quality of course. Class is very uninteresting and attendance is mandatory, beware.
